Merafe Resources, Metorex and Santam: South African Equity Market Preview

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-02-28T22:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/merafe-resources-metorex-santam-south-african-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  South Africa’s FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index advanced for
a second day, gaining 306.50, or 1 percent, to 32,272.09 at the
5 p.m. close in Johannesburg, taking its gain in the month to
2.8 percent.    Merafe Resources Ltd . (MRF SJ): The ferrochrome mining
company reports earnings results for the year ended December.
Merafe said on Jan. 27 it was expecting to report earnings per
share of between 10 cents and 12 cents for the year, compared
with a loss per share of 6 cents for the year earlier. Merafe
rose 5 cents, or 3.2 percent, to 1.60 rand.    Metorex Ltd . (MTX SJ): The copper and cobalt mining company
publishes an earnings statement for the 18-months through
December 31. Metorex, which changed its financial year end to
December, from June, said on Feb. 11 that it expected earnings
per share to be as high as 1.03 rand for the period. The stock
gained 6 cents, or 1.1 percent, to 5.70 rand.    Santam Ltd . (SNT SJ): South Africa’s largest property and
casualty insurer releases earnings for the year through
December. Santam said it expects per share earnings for the
period to be up to 55 percent higher than the year earlier,
according to a trading update dated Feb. 16. The stock climbed
3.43 rand, or 2.8 percent, to 127.96 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
